<HL>
   Net Loss of American
   Confectionery Corp.
   Narrowed in Quarter
</HL>
<DATE>
05/15/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   CNDY
</CO>
<IN>
DOW JONES INTERVIEW (CEO)
</IN>
<LP>
   SACRAMENTO, Calif. -- After recent purchases of nut, candy
and yogurt companies, American Confectionery Corp. expects to
report a reduced net loss for the fiscal third quarter ended
March 31, Steve Kircher, president, said.
   For the latest quarter, American Confectionery expects to
report a net loss in the range of $900,000, or about 18 cents
a share, compared with a year-earlier loss of $1 million, or
about 21 cents, including respectively scaled-down net losses
from continuing operations of $284,000, or five cents a
share, and $726,000, or 15 cents a share. Besides the effect
of acquisitions, Mr. Kircher said results have been skewed by
a continuing strategy of converting company-owned stores to
franchised operations, which is reducing revenue in the
near-term.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   "It is real clear that the core business is getting
better," Mr. Kircher said, noting that the company's retail
nut business, which had been operating at an annual $17
million loss when acquired in November 1988, was currently
breaking even.
   In the latest quarter, Mr. Kircher said revenue would
approximate $6 million, compared with about $8 million a year
earlier, with revenue from continuing operations increasing
to about $4.6 million, from $4.3 million.
   Mr. Kircher said results for the nine months would be
"break-even to a small loss" compared with year-earlier
profit of $1.1 million, or about 21 cents. Nine months
revenue would be flat, or would slightly exceed the $25
million reported a year ago, and would increase to $17.4
million, from about $11 million on a continuing basis. Unlike
a year earlier, the latest quarter and nine months didn't
include the Easter holiday, an important time for candy
sales.
   American Confectionery became publicly held in March, with
the acquisition of J. Higby's Inc., an unprofitable
franchiser of frozen yogurt and specialty foods stores.
</TEXT>
