<LP>
   Hurco Cos., citing market-share gains both in domestic and
overseas markets, said net income climbed 42% in the second
quarter, ended April 30, on a 14% increase in revenue.
   The Indianapolis maker of computer-controlled machine tool
systems said net income was $2.5 million, or 45 cents a
share, up from the year-earlier $1.8 million, or 40 cents a
share. Per-share figures reflect an increase in average
shares outstanding to 5.7 million from 4.5 million.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Revenue was $24.8 million in the latest period, up from
$21.9 million.
   Orders were $22.6 million in the latest period, up 13%.
   For the six months, Hurco's net income rose 54% to $4.7
million, or 83 cents a share, from the year-earlier $3.1
million, or 69 cents a share on fewer shares outstanding.
Six-month revenue was $47.6 million, up 18% from the
year-earlier $40.3 million.
