   "While we expect excellent results for the remainder of
the year," said Reginald F. Lewis, chief executive officer,
"our second- and third-quarter figures will determine our
full-year performance because our ice-cream and dessert
products are sold during the warm-weather period." TLC sells
a number of European food products including Tato snack foods
in Ireland and Samson ice cream in Italy.
   In December, TLC canceled a proposed initial public
offering as large investors shunned the plan. The company,
formed two years prior as an investor group led by Mr. Lewis
purchased what had been the foreign-food lines of Beatrice
Cos. from investment bank Kohlberg Kravis Roberts &amp; Co.
