<LP>
   Mission Insurance Group Inc. said a federal court approved
the company's rehabilitation agreement for unit Mission
Insurance Cos. that, among other things, calls for the
transfer of $29 million in assets to government trusts.
   The Los Angeles-based insurer has been in bankruptcy-law
proceedings since 1987. Its insolvency was one of the largest
insurance-company failures in history.
</LP>
