   The California Insurance Commission must resolve certain
tax issues in connection with the plan.
   Under the plan, the assets and liabilities of Mission
Insurance Cos. will be transferred to trusts overseen by the
California insurance commissioner. The transfer is to include
$14 million in cash and 5.9 million Mission Insurance Group
common shares, representing about 29% of the stock
outstanding.
