<HL>
   Spain's CPI Rose 0.2% in April
</HL>
<DATE>
05/15/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A6
</SO>
<CO>
   EUROP
</CO>
<LP>
   MADRID -- Spain's consumer price index rose 0.2% in April
from March despite a sharp drop in food prices, the country's
National Statistics Institute said.
   The monthly increase brings Spain's year-to-year inflation
rate to 7%, unchanged from March and down from 7.3% in
February.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Prices excluding food prices climbed 0.7% in April from
March. Food prices fell 0.6% in April from March with the
year-onyear increase in food prices at 7.4% at the end of
April.
   The inflation figures fell within analysts' expectations,
which called for a rise in the CPI of between 0.2% and 0.4%.
   At the end of April, the consumer price index stood at
161.8 from 161.4 in March. The index is based on 1983 equals
100.
</TEXT>
